WEBVTT

00:21.891 --> 00:23.458
[distant sirens blaring]

00:33.946 --> 00:35.426
[man] Cancel the noise.

00:38.255 --> 00:39.387
Listen.

00:41.258 --> 00:42.694
Music's everywhere.

00:45.480 --> 00:48.004
We breathe and we swallow
with the place.

00:49.919 --> 00:51.225
Pay attention to it.

00:53.488 --> 00:55.142
Do let it connect.

00:56.969 --> 01:00.973
There's a pleasing
combination of elements.

01:01.104 --> 01:04.238
They all have different callers
and different sounds.

01:05.717 --> 01:07.154
Listen to them.

01:08.676 --> 01:10.635
There is a deep structure.

01:13.334 --> 01:14.987
Music aligned.

01:15.118 --> 01:17.468
The harmony
that complements the melody.

01:19.295 --> 01:21.298
Don't pay attention
to the noise.

01:23.779 --> 01:25.085
That is only noise.

01:27.304 --> 01:29.480
Concentrate your attention.

01:31.526 --> 01:33.702
Recalibrate your mind.

01:35.269 --> 01:36.661
Music is inside.

01:39.533 --> 01:41.536
It resides inside of you.

01:43.625 --> 01:45.279
Just feel it.

01:48.108 --> 01:49.718
Just sense it.

01:52.590 --> 01:53.983
Embrace it.

01:56.681 --> 01:59.684
It's coming from you.
It's coming from your heart.

02:01.773 --> 02:03.949
Music is right there.

02:05.603 --> 02:07.344
That's what I learned from you.

02:10.217 --> 02:12.828
[emcee] Hello, everyone.
Welcome to Minton's Playhouse,

02:12.871 --> 02:16.658
the most iconic jazz parlor
in Harlem, New York City,

02:16.788 --> 02:19.226
the United States,
and the world.

02:19.269 --> 02:21.532
Minton's was
established in 1938.

02:21.663 --> 02:25.579
We are celebrating 81 years
of musical legacy.

02:26.102 --> 02:28.626
Today we have
a very special guest,

02:28.757 --> 02:31.325
He is a great
Cuban-American singer,

02:31.454 --> 02:35.372
so please, help me welcome
Mr. Nico Quevedo.

02:36.547 --> 02:38.158
[cheers and applause]

02:41.596 --> 02:43.466
[whooping]

02:56.045 --> 02:57.351
Thank you for that.

02:59.004 --> 03:00.180
You know, this moment...

03:01.920 --> 03:03.705
...right here, right now...

03:05.272 --> 03:07.970
...is all we have.

03:08.013 --> 03:09.189
It's all we are.

03:11.234 --> 03:13.323
This night.

03:13.454 --> 03:15.978
So let's have fun tonight.
Right?

03:16.065 --> 03:19.590
[cheering]

03:19.634 --> 03:21.418
Let's give it up for the band.

03:27.468 --> 03:28.947
[cheering continues]

03:31.733 --> 03:33.822
Now this song,

03:33.865 --> 03:36.520
this one's special for me,

03:36.607 --> 03:39.697
because I couldn't sing
this song in a while.

03:39.828 --> 03:43.048
And as we said,
tonight is the night.

03:44.876 --> 03:47.314
As the old ones
used to say in Cuba,

03:47.444 --> 03:50.665
if you want your rumba
to be profound,

03:50.708 --> 03:54.059
you have to learn how to sing
out of your own pain.

03:54.103 --> 03:55.974
You want your rumba
to be heard,

03:56.105 --> 03:58.542
let the drums cry your sorrow.

03:58.586 --> 04:01.328
Allow your heart
to sing your blues.

04:06.202 --> 04:09.161
I made this song

04:09.292 --> 04:12.556
when I learned how to
transform my pain into music.

04:22.523 --> 04:28.616
[singing in Spanish]

05:39.207 --> 05:41.166
[in English] You
have to help me on this.

05:43.908 --> 05:45.519
I really need you.

05:50.567 --> 05:51.873
[man] Nico!

05:52.700 --> 05:54.397
Nico.

05:55.006 --> 05:56.094
[speaking Spanish]

05:56.312 --> 05:57.574
Yeah.

06:28.736 --> 06:31.956
♪

06:40.661 --> 06:42.489
[singing in Spanish]

08:29.334 --> 08:31.380
[speaking in Spanish]

08:33.730 --> 08:34.514
[in English]

08:35.732 --> 08:38.605
Yeah, why not?
I'll take it to go, though.

08:41.825 --> 08:43.304
-Thank you.
-Go?

08:43.479 --> 08:45.873
[speaking Spanish]

08:45.960 --> 08:48.049
[chuckles]

08:48.092 --> 08:51.400
Good old days, huh?
Good old days are gone, Chino.

08:51.443 --> 08:54.142
I'll pay for it next week.
Thank you.

08:54.272 --> 08:57.188
♪

09:14.379 --> 09:15.903
[indistinct chatter]

09:24.607 --> 09:26.783
[pensive music playing]

09:34.965 --> 09:38.229
[chatting in Spanish]

09:48.370 --> 09:50.546
[in English]

09:50.590 --> 09:51.939
[speaking Spanish]

09:54.855 --> 09:57.379
[in English]

09:59.468 --> 10:01.557
You're cheating on the world.

10:01.688 --> 10:03.864
[argument continues in Spanish]

10:03.994 --> 10:04.778
What are you talking about?

10:04.908 --> 10:08.042
♪

10:11.654 --> 10:14.614
♪

10:30.107 --> 10:31.500
I don't get it.

10:36.810 --> 10:38.507
I don't fucking get it!

10:51.607 --> 10:53.870
You said you were gonna
help me on this.

10:56.046 --> 10:58.092
You told me that.

11:00.311 --> 11:03.053
You're full of shit.

11:03.097 --> 11:05.839
Full of... Fuck.

11:08.276 --> 11:10.495
I have to endure
all this by myself,

11:10.539 --> 11:12.323
and you can't even
keep your word?

11:13.890 --> 11:16.371
What's wrong with you?

11:16.501 --> 11:18.025
What's the matter?

11:24.596 --> 11:26.642
I stayed here because of you.

11:28.775 --> 11:31.473
We had something.
It was something special.

11:32.126 --> 11:33.344
It was real.

11:34.345 --> 11:36.130
What do I have now?

11:36.173 --> 11:39.220
Nothing. I have nothing.

11:39.263 --> 11:41.178
You don't wanna talk to me.
You don't wanna listen to me.

11:41.309 --> 11:43.833
You don't wanna pay attention
to me. You don't wanna help me.

11:43.964 --> 11:47.489
What do you want?
What the fuck do you want?!

11:57.238 --> 11:59.022
You want rum?

12:01.895 --> 12:04.027
Let me get you
a little bit of rum.

12:17.171 --> 12:18.607
[exhales deeply]

12:19.956 --> 12:23.046
[sniffles, exhales deeply]

12:23.133 --> 12:26.746
[inhales sharply]
You wanna go to the beach?

12:26.789 --> 12:28.835
Hmm?

12:28.922 --> 12:31.098
I can take you
to a baseball game if you want.

12:32.839 --> 12:34.754
We can have drinks.

12:36.712 --> 12:38.845
We can go out.

12:38.932 --> 12:41.282
We can have fun.
Is that what you want?

12:44.067 --> 12:45.373
Huh?

12:51.858 --> 12:54.730
[blowing air]

12:54.774 --> 12:56.340
[shells rattling]

13:06.002 --> 13:07.438
[exhales heavily]

13:10.615 --> 13:13.749
What do you want?
What the fuck do you want?!

13:13.793 --> 13:15.838
What do you want?!

13:22.758 --> 13:23.890
You...

13:24.020 --> 13:27.415
You're not clear with me.

13:29.678 --> 13:31.680
There's just no
communication at all.

13:34.117 --> 13:35.858
You don't wanna be
my friend no more?

13:39.253 --> 13:40.167
Why?

13:41.733 --> 13:43.866
Why are you doing this to me?
Why?

13:49.480 --> 13:51.047
I can't sing.

13:54.834 --> 13:58.489
I can't... write.

13:58.576 --> 14:04.887
I can't... I cannot play
because I don't feel it.

14:07.107 --> 14:09.283
I don't have it no more.

14:16.159 --> 14:17.857
I don't have...

14:17.944 --> 14:21.034
Don't take that away
from me, bro.

14:24.167 --> 14:29.085
Don't take it away from me
because that's all I have.

14:29.259 --> 14:30.652
That's all I have.

14:31.958 --> 14:33.437
Don't take it away.

14:37.746 --> 14:39.835
Don't take it away from me.

14:42.969 --> 14:44.405
[sobbing]

14:44.535 --> 14:47.321
[sad music playing]

14:51.107 --> 14:53.109
Don't take it away from me.

14:54.806 --> 14:55.895
[whispering]
Don't take it away.

14:55.982 --> 14:59.202
♪

15:17.786 --> 15:21.137
[drumming in distance]

15:30.973 --> 15:33.715
[indistinct chatter in Spanish]

15:38.372 --> 15:39.547
[drumming continues]

15:39.590 --> 15:41.288
[chatter continues]

15:51.167 --> 15:53.474
[singing in Spanish]

15:53.648 --> 15:56.346
[crowd singing in Spanish]

16:33.688 --> 16:34.950
[speaking Spanish]

16:43.219 --> 16:45.091
Thank you.

16:45.178 --> 16:48.398
Hey, really cool music, Nicolas.
Nicolas, is it?

16:48.442 --> 16:50.835
Yeah. Yeah.

16:50.879 --> 16:53.316
Man, I heard you're not even
from around here.

16:53.360 --> 16:55.971
I was born in Jersey,
but I'm Cuban.

16:56.102 --> 16:57.277
And what brought you
back out here?

16:57.407 --> 17:00.062
Well, you know, oh, music.

17:00.106 --> 17:03.196
Well, listen.
You got that music thing down.

17:03.239 --> 17:06.068
Is it all, like, your music?

17:06.112 --> 17:07.461
-[greeting in Spanish]
-Eh.

17:07.635 --> 17:09.289
Wrote it with my best friend.

17:09.332 --> 17:11.638
Anyway, listen.
Really, really cool music.

17:11.769 --> 17:14.858
-I'm Bob Arenas, by the way.
-Ah, Nicolas [indistinct].

17:14.903 --> 17:17.036
So which one
was he in the band,

17:17.123 --> 17:20.213
your friend in the band?

17:20.343 --> 17:23.520
He's dead.
Passed away three months ago.

17:23.651 --> 17:27.133
Sorry about that, man.
I-I didn't know.

17:27.262 --> 17:28.786
What was his name?

17:30.832 --> 17:32.138
Celso.

17:33.139 --> 17:35.010
Celso Quiñones.

17:35.793 --> 17:38.535
-It was nice meeting you.
-Um...

17:38.666 --> 17:40.537
Hey, you know...

17:40.668 --> 17:43.062
I'm a music manager
and producer in New York.

17:43.149 --> 17:44.976
Check it out.

17:45.107 --> 17:48.241
[children shouting playfully
in distance]

17:48.371 --> 17:51.505
Listen, I would like to discuss
with you the possibility

17:51.548 --> 17:54.160
of bringing you back
out there, man.

17:54.247 --> 17:56.162
I really like what you have,
seriously,

17:56.292 --> 17:58.512
and I think New York
is a better market--

17:58.599 --> 18:01.123
Look, I'm--
I'm not interested.

18:01.254 --> 18:04.039
You must be
the only Cuban musician

18:04.170 --> 18:05.910
that has no interest
in getting out of here.

18:05.954 --> 18:08.043
-Gotta go. Thank you.
-Hey, Nico.

18:08.174 --> 18:10.176
Just...
Listen, think about it.

18:10.263 --> 18:12.526
The number in the back
is where I'm staying.

18:12.569 --> 18:14.136
Check out the back.

18:14.180 --> 18:17.357
If you change your mind,
hit me up.

18:17.487 --> 18:20.447
I can help you. Trust me.

18:29.891 --> 18:31.458
Nico!

18:32.981 --> 18:35.157
[emotional music playing]

18:45.124 --> 18:48.083
I thought I would never
see you again.

18:48.127 --> 18:50.477
I promised
I was gonna come back.

18:52.218 --> 18:54.524
Yeah.

18:54.568 --> 18:56.570
That was four years ago.

18:56.657 --> 18:58.093
I never said when.

18:58.137 --> 19:00.356
[speaking Spanish]

19:00.400 --> 19:02.663
[replying in Spanish]

19:28.036 --> 19:30.212
And I had a good teacher.

19:30.343 --> 19:34.347
♪

19:42.877 --> 19:45.053
I can't believe he's gone.

19:45.184 --> 19:47.360
[sighs] Yep.

19:50.014 --> 19:52.408
[sighs]
We had good times together.

19:59.676 --> 20:01.417
Ahh.

20:01.461 --> 20:04.203
We wanted
to change the world with music.

20:05.856 --> 20:08.816
We wanted to take all this...

20:08.859 --> 20:11.427
our roots, our background,
the poetry,

20:11.514 --> 20:14.822
and to put it out there.

20:14.865 --> 20:17.825
I wanted to understand
who I was, and now...

20:19.087 --> 20:22.786
I don't even know who I am.

20:22.873 --> 20:26.181
And then... cancer.

20:28.314 --> 20:30.316
Cancer took everything from him.

20:34.320 --> 20:36.800
I took care of him all the way
to the end, you know.

20:38.324 --> 20:39.499
One day...

20:39.629 --> 20:43.067
One day we were celebrating
his last birthday,

20:43.111 --> 20:46.984
and I sang a song
I wrote for him.

20:47.115 --> 20:51.337
When I finished, he looked
at me in the eye and he said...

20:53.774 --> 20:56.037
"You have to promise me.
You have to promise me that

20:56.429 --> 21:00.563
no matter what,

21:00.650 --> 21:04.872
you'll never stop doing this."
And I said, "I promise."

21:04.915 --> 21:07.483
And then, his last day...

21:10.225 --> 21:11.531
...his last day,

21:11.661 --> 21:12.880
the pain was killing him.

21:17.537 --> 21:19.669
I didn't know...
[clears throat]

21:20.757 --> 21:24.631
I didn't know what to do
to relieve his pain, you know?

21:35.032 --> 21:36.643
And I sang that song for him.

21:43.171 --> 21:45.086
He was calm. He was...

21:46.957 --> 21:49.090
He was... breathing.

21:50.961 --> 21:53.747
He smiled... again.

21:59.274 --> 22:01.972
That was the last song
I could write.

22:04.192 --> 22:09.284
♪

22:09.415 --> 22:12.548
That was the last time
I could sing from my heart.

22:14.202 --> 22:18.337
♪

23:42.682 --> 23:44.074
I needed this.

23:45.641 --> 23:46.860
Me?

23:48.035 --> 23:49.384
[laughing]

23:50.864 --> 23:52.648
No.

23:52.735 --> 23:54.476
I needed to be back home.

24:01.527 --> 24:04.660
My life there is not what
it used to be here.

24:06.880 --> 24:08.229
Sometimes I...

24:10.187 --> 24:11.667
I feel out of place.

24:13.364 --> 24:17.586
We're always
gonna feel out of place.

24:17.717 --> 24:19.327
We're always
gonna need something

24:19.414 --> 24:20.894
because we're immigrants.

24:22.765 --> 24:24.898
When are you heading back
to New York?

24:24.941 --> 24:26.029
Tomorrow.

24:29.206 --> 24:31.470
If you ever go back,
you should call me.

24:31.557 --> 24:33.167
-I will.
-Right!

24:33.341 --> 24:35.691
-Yeah, I promise I will.
-Mm-hmm.

24:37.563 --> 24:39.260
That's what you said
when I left.

24:40.696 --> 24:44.004
You and Celso were gonna
make it to the States.

24:45.832 --> 24:48.487
You wanted to bring
all your music to New York.

24:53.143 --> 24:54.623
What happened to that dream?

24:55.145 --> 24:56.930
[percussion beating]

24:57.800 --> 24:59.367
[singing in Spanish]

25:48.459 --> 25:51.114
Hey, Bob, it's me. Nicolas.

25:51.941 --> 25:55.641
Yeah. You blew me away
with your talent, Nicolas.

25:55.771 --> 25:58.426
No, man, you're very special.

25:58.513 --> 26:00.820
You have something
really special, man.

26:00.994 --> 26:02.822
-Thanks.
-Nah, don't thank me.

26:02.952 --> 26:03.997
We're doing business, my friend.

26:05.041 --> 26:07.740
Aha!

26:07.870 --> 26:12.092
Now, see, I usually
charge my clients 50%

26:12.135 --> 26:14.529
for management and production
and that type of thing,

26:14.660 --> 26:17.010
but I understand
your particular situation,

26:17.097 --> 26:21.362
so I'm willing to lower my fee
to 30% of your profits.

26:23.886 --> 26:28.587
-Thirty percent?
-Off the gross, of course.

26:28.674 --> 26:30.893
But... hey, look,

26:31.024 --> 26:34.593
the good thing is,
as soon as you get to New York,

26:34.680 --> 26:36.595
you'll have a job.

26:36.638 --> 26:40.555
-Huh? Isn't that somethin'?
-Yeah.

26:40.686 --> 26:43.297
Isn't it crazy how two
Americans can close on a deal

26:43.427 --> 26:45.908
out here in this place,
out in Cuba?

26:46.039 --> 26:49.999
-Yeah. It's a new time.
-Hell, yeah. [chuckles]

26:50.043 --> 26:53.133
Listen, I gotta talk to you
about something else.

26:53.263 --> 26:54.700
What's that?

26:54.787 --> 26:57.224
I don't have a place
to stay in New York.

26:57.267 --> 27:00.096
Say no more. You look for me.

27:00.227 --> 27:02.490
Okay?
Mi casa es su casa,baby.

27:02.577 --> 27:04.274
You got that right.
You got it right.

27:04.361 --> 27:05.711
-You know what I'm saying?
-Right. Yes.

27:05.841 --> 27:07.277
-Huh?
-Yeah, you got it right.

27:07.364 --> 27:09.497
Excuse me, sir.
There's someone waiting for you.

27:11.760 --> 27:14.328
I have to go, man.
I have to get out.

27:14.458 --> 27:17.113
It's my last night,
and I got a very special date,

27:17.244 --> 27:20.421
but I'll see you in New York.
Yes?

27:20.508 --> 27:24.294
-Yes, sir.
-All right.

27:24.338 --> 27:28.516
You're very special, Nicolas.
Don't forget it.

27:33.652 --> 27:35.305
[background chatter]

27:54.411 --> 27:57.893
Looks like we're going
to New York.

27:57.980 --> 28:01.723
[fast tempo music playing]

28:01.767 --> 28:02.506
[women]
♪ Come on, come on

28:02.550 --> 28:03.986
[singing in Spanish]

28:04.117 --> 28:06.554
[sirens blaring in distance]

28:06.597 --> 28:10.123
[women continue singing
in Spanish]

28:10.166 --> 28:13.256
♪

28:25.878 --> 28:29.359
[women continues singing
in Spanish]

29:02.915 --> 29:05.744
[woman] Hey,
can you open the door?

29:05.831 --> 29:08.007
[knocking]

29:08.050 --> 29:09.835
[woman] Hey,
are you fucking deaf?

29:09.965 --> 29:11.488
Answer the door.

29:11.619 --> 29:13.577
[child] Mom!
I'm in the bathroom.

29:13.708 --> 29:15.188
[woman] Fuck!

29:15.275 --> 29:17.451
This is the third time
you've been in bathroom today.

29:17.494 --> 29:20.584
I swear you spend more time on
the toilet than anywhere else.

29:22.630 --> 29:24.850
Hey.

29:24.937 --> 29:28.767
-What do you fucking need?
-Oh! Is, uh, Bob here?

29:29.942 --> 29:32.466
No. I haven't seen
that piece of shit in months.

29:32.509 --> 29:36.165
-What do you need him for?
-Well... I'm-- My name is Nico.

29:36.296 --> 29:38.167
And Bob and I met
a few months ago in Cuba.

29:38.211 --> 29:40.953
He offered me a contract
to come and work with him.

29:41.083 --> 29:42.955
-I'm sorry. Did you say Cuba?
-Yeah.

29:42.998 --> 29:45.305
Yeah, Cuba. I was...
I was living in Cuba,

29:45.435 --> 29:47.611
and he saw me perform in the
streets when he approached me.

29:47.742 --> 29:50.005
-In Cuba?
-Yes, in Cuba.

29:50.049 --> 29:51.441
Yeah. When was this?

29:51.485 --> 29:54.096
Well, as I said,
a few months ago.

29:54.140 --> 29:58.013
Fuck. I told you your father
was a piece of shit!

29:58.057 --> 29:59.667
[child] What?

29:59.754 --> 30:01.234
He was supposed to be
at a spiritual retreat,

30:01.321 --> 30:02.975
trying to find himself,
and you're telling me he was

30:03.105 --> 30:04.890
messing around with you,
blowing lines

30:04.977 --> 30:07.675
and banging whores in Cuba,
you fucking piece of garbage!

30:07.806 --> 30:09.459
[child]
What? Mom, who's that?

30:09.546 --> 30:11.200
Oh! There's some fucking
animal here that says

30:11.244 --> 30:14.290
he's been with your father
in Cuba a few months ago

30:14.334 --> 30:16.727
when your fucking father
was supposed to be in Ohio,

30:16.858 --> 30:19.426
saving his fucking soul.
-What are you talking about?

30:19.469 --> 30:22.298
He's been fucking whoring around
behind my back?

30:22.429 --> 30:24.648
Again?

30:24.779 --> 30:27.129
Seriously?!

30:27.260 --> 30:29.262
Again?

30:29.305 --> 30:31.133
You know, he told me after
Colombia he wouldn't do it,

30:31.177 --> 30:34.920
but here we are.
You fucking piece of cocksucker!

30:34.963 --> 30:38.184
-I-I-I--
-Don't talk to me, you pervert.

30:38.314 --> 30:40.099
You were what, making
a mockery of me with him?

30:40.142 --> 30:41.927
-No. I--
-Down in Cuba, having a party.

30:42.014 --> 30:43.798
Now you're coming to my house.
What, you wanna do it here?

30:43.929 --> 30:46.583
-No, I'm just a musician.
-Stop!

30:46.714 --> 30:48.281
