and here I am.

59:32.743 --> 59:34.788
When did you get here?

59:36.877 --> 59:39.663
Like, 24 hours ago.

59:40.881 --> 59:42.796
Twenty-four hours ago?

59:42.883 --> 59:45.843
[laughs] You're still fresh.

59:45.973 --> 59:48.410
-Yes.
-Joe, give my friend...

59:49.629 --> 59:50.804
Nico.

59:53.633 --> 59:57.245
Give my friend Nico a shot.

59:57.289 --> 59:59.770
-Rum?
-Rum is always good.

1:00:01.641 --> 1:00:04.470
Come on.

1:00:04.557 --> 1:00:06.167
Come on. It's on the house.
It's okay.

1:00:13.044 --> 1:00:14.436
Thank you.

1:00:17.265 --> 1:00:19.180
-Thanks.
-Okay.

1:00:28.625 --> 1:00:29.626
Cheers.

1:00:29.669 --> 1:00:33.804
Salut.

1:00:33.847 --> 1:00:36.110
So, Nico... [clears throat]

1:00:36.241 --> 1:00:38.852
what brings you back?

1:00:41.072 --> 1:00:42.290
This place.

1:00:44.815 --> 1:00:47.165
[sighs]

1:00:47.208 --> 1:00:49.471
Somebody told me about
this place a few years ago.

1:00:56.783 --> 1:00:58.655
I always wanted to come
and see it by myself.

1:01:05.096 --> 1:01:06.663
[saxophone playing]

1:01:11.319 --> 1:01:14.496
Interesting...

1:01:14.540 --> 1:01:17.848
how life gives you what you need
at the right time you need it.

1:01:19.545 --> 1:01:22.069
I remember when I was a kid...

1:01:25.594 --> 1:01:28.685
my father used to play sax
right here in this place.

1:01:31.644 --> 1:01:34.734
I'd run out from the house
in the middle of the night

1:01:35.213 --> 1:01:36.954
and stand right there,

1:01:37.737 --> 1:01:41.262
by the bar entrance
and watch him play.

1:01:43.569 --> 1:01:46.224
I can assume clearly
because the place was packed,

1:01:46.354 --> 1:01:51.446
but, oh, I could hear him
play that sax, man.

1:01:53.318 --> 1:01:55.276
That was magic to my ears.

1:01:57.017 --> 1:01:58.279
Those nights...

1:02:00.455 --> 1:02:03.807
after watching him play
for two hours...

1:02:07.027 --> 1:02:10.727
I ran back home
after his last solo,

1:02:10.814 --> 1:02:14.295
and... I got home and...

1:02:16.254 --> 1:02:19.387
...later on I didn't hear the
door slam behind him like usual.

1:02:19.518 --> 1:02:24.131
♪

1:02:24.175 --> 1:02:25.567
Never came back home.

1:02:27.700 --> 1:02:29.920
That was the last time
I saw him.

1:02:32.487 --> 1:02:34.054
You never heard from him?

1:02:35.839 --> 1:02:38.537
No. Never again.

1:02:42.584 --> 1:02:46.153
But the Blue Bird
was always on my mind.

1:02:51.506 --> 1:02:55.510
I wanted to be a musician,
but I didn't have the skills,

1:02:55.554 --> 1:02:57.208
didn't have the endowment.

1:02:59.123 --> 1:03:01.952
But, man, did I have
the skills to make money.

1:03:02.082 --> 1:03:05.738
That's what I did.
I made a lot of money,

1:03:05.782 --> 1:03:07.696
and bought this place.

1:03:07.827 --> 1:03:09.089
How did you get that flyer?

1:03:10.874 --> 1:03:12.179
My friend, Celso.

1:03:14.616 --> 1:03:15.835
He gave it to me.

1:03:19.883 --> 1:03:21.623
Celso?

1:03:21.667 --> 1:03:23.800
-Yeah.
-That's a strange name.

1:03:26.890 --> 1:03:29.109
-How'd he get it?
-His mom.

1:03:29.240 --> 1:03:31.111
Hmm.

1:03:33.940 --> 1:03:39.990
So I printed these flyers
back in '82.

1:03:40.033 --> 1:03:41.469
After I acquired the place,

1:03:41.556 --> 1:03:43.689
I took some of these
down to the island.

1:03:43.732 --> 1:03:46.387
You know, do a little
advertising, stuff like that.

1:03:46.518 --> 1:03:50.957
Matter of fact, I was
planning to hire some locals,

1:03:51.088 --> 1:03:55.614
great musicians, come back here,
but it was the '80s, so...

1:03:57.964 --> 1:04:00.184
It's a cool thing
that your friend kept this.

1:04:02.664 --> 1:04:05.232
-He like jazz?
-He loves jazz.

1:04:08.061 --> 1:04:09.193
That makes sense.

1:04:10.890 --> 1:04:12.587
As a matter of fact, he's so...

1:04:16.113 --> 1:04:18.506
well...

1:04:18.593 --> 1:04:23.337
He was... a great composer.

1:04:23.468 --> 1:04:25.818
Really? What kinda music?

1:04:25.862 --> 1:04:28.429
Rumba Cubana.

1:04:28.516 --> 1:04:30.910
Yeah, Rumba Cubana.

1:04:31.041 --> 1:04:34.653
I love Rumba Cubana.

1:04:34.740 --> 1:04:36.873
Yes, I know.

1:04:36.916 --> 1:04:39.136
You do?

1:04:39.179 --> 1:04:42.052
I do... know a lot of things
about you.

1:04:46.970 --> 1:04:50.625
I didn't think
I was that famous.

1:04:50.756 --> 1:04:52.497
See my friend, Celso...

1:04:55.761 --> 1:04:59.765
he always wanted
to come here to New York,

1:04:59.852 --> 1:05:04.422
He was fascinated, he was
mesmerized, he was obsessed

1:05:04.552 --> 1:05:06.119
with the idea of the Blue Bird.

1:05:11.081 --> 1:05:13.213
He passed away a few months ago.

1:05:14.693 --> 1:05:15.781
Yeah.

1:05:18.740 --> 1:05:19.959
Sorry to hear that.

1:05:22.396 --> 1:05:25.225
You know what's interesting?
This place, the Blue Bird,

1:05:25.399 --> 1:05:28.750
