that he had with his father.

1:05:33.146 --> 1:05:35.714
He went away without
even knowing about him.

1:05:42.242 --> 1:05:43.983
It was this flyer right here...

1:05:45.811 --> 1:05:48.248
the only thing
he ever got from his dad.

1:05:52.252 --> 1:05:54.080
You gave this flyer to Mercedes,

1:05:54.211 --> 1:05:58.432
the beautiful woman
you met and fell in love with,

1:05:58.563 --> 1:06:00.173
when you went to Cuba.

1:06:01.392 --> 1:06:03.655
This flyer...

1:06:03.785 --> 1:06:06.310
was the only thing
that Celso got to see from you.

1:06:08.051 --> 1:06:09.530
You had a son in Cuba.

1:06:11.837 --> 1:06:13.534
But you never came back.

1:06:16.363 --> 1:06:17.408
Never came back.

1:06:19.627 --> 1:06:22.935
And all those years,
Mercedes only hoped

1:06:23.066 --> 1:06:25.372
that one day you would
come back to see your son.

1:06:28.941 --> 1:06:30.987
Almost a year and a half ago...

1:06:34.033 --> 1:06:37.732
Celso got cancer, and she died.

1:06:37.863 --> 1:06:41.736
I always knew
what his biggest dream was,

1:06:42.085 --> 1:06:43.347
that's why I'm here.

1:07:03.062 --> 1:07:04.063
This...

1:07:06.544 --> 1:07:07.849
...is Celso's ashes.

1:07:13.203 --> 1:07:14.987
This is your son.

1:07:23.865 --> 1:07:25.563
[saxophone playing continues]

1:07:27.913 --> 1:07:29.654
